name: Susi Kentikian
bio:
When it comes to the world of boxing, there are names that become synonymous with skill, determination, and success. One name that stands out is Susi Kentikian. Born on September 11, 1987, Kentikian has made a name for herself in the flyweight division with her remarkable talent and unwavering dedication. Standing at 155cm tall, this orthodox fighter has proven time and time again that she is a force to be reckoned with in the ring.

A fighter's nickname often adds character and intrigue to their persona, and Susi Kentikian is no exception. Known as "Susi," this moniker reflects her fierce spirit and tenacity inside the squared circle. With each fight, she brings a level of intensity and determination that truly sets her apart from her opponents.

As a boxer, Kentikian competes in the flyweight weight class. This weight class, which ranges from 108 to 112 pounds, is known for its speed and agility. It requires fighters to possess a unique blend of strength and quickness in order to excel. For Susi Kentikian, this weight class has become her domain, and she has proven herself time and time again as a formidable contender.

One aspect of a boxer's style that can greatly affect their success is their stance. Susi Kentikian fights in the orthodox stance, which means she leads with her left hand and her right hand serves as her power punch. This stance allows her to generate power and deliver devastating blows to her opponents.

Throughout her career, Susi Kentikian has faced off against some of the best fighters in her weight class. Her skills and determination have earned her numerous victories and accolades, solidifying her position among the elite in the boxing world. But what makes her so unique and captivating as a fighter?

One of the factors that sets Susi Kentikian apart is her fighting style. Known for her aggressive and relentless approach, she never backs down from a challenge. Whether it's delivering lightning-fast combinations or absorbing her opponent's punches with an iron will, Kentikian's style of boxing is as thrilling as it is effective.

Another aspect of Kentikian's boxing prowess is her ability to adapt and overcome adversity in the ring. Boxing can be a grueling and unforgiving sport, but Susi has shown time and time again that she has what it takes to rise above challenges. She possesses a remarkable mental fortitude that allows her to stay focused and composed even in the face of adversity.

But it's not all about the physical and mental aspects of boxing that make Susi Kentikian a true champion. It's also her heart and dedication to the sport. Boxing is demanding both physically and mentally, requiring countless hours of training and preparation. Kentikian's unwavering commitment to her craft is evident in her performances and results.

Throughout her career, Susi Kentikian has captured the hearts of boxing fans around the world with her electrifying performances and undeniable talent. She has proven herself to be a true force to be reckoned with in the flyweight division, and her legacy will undoubtedly continue to grow.

So, the next time you step into the boxing ring or watch a flyweight bout, remember the name Susi Kentikian. She is more than just a boxer â€“ she is a symbol of determination, skill, and unwavering passion for the sport. Watch her unleash her fury with each punch, and witness boxing greatness in the form of "Susi."
